The Giver of Names, the Bestower of Wit, the Slayer of the Thunderbird, the Creator of Lies, the Sun-Stealer - the Trickster of all Tricksters - looked up from his altar, and saw what was happening. 

The deity laughed - a cacophonous laugh that echoed towards the stars - the very ones he placed there eons ago.
